# No Planning After GenerateImage

When the Sighted SVG pipeline is active (color-map.json and recolor-map.json exist for the ad):

1. Your tool call IMMEDIATELY after `GenerateImage` MUST be a `Shell` call running `sighted-pipeline.js`
2. Do NOT write any text between GenerateImage and the Shell call
3. Do NOT comment on the generated image
4. Do NOT say "let me verify" or "good reference image"
5. Do NOT copy the file manually — the pipeline auto-archives the reference

```
GenerateImage → Shell (sighted-pipeline.js with absolute path from GenerateImage) → Read preview.png
```

The pipeline accepts any absolute path as input. Pass the GenerateImage output path directly:

```bash
node scripts/sighted-pipeline.js "<ABSOLUTE_PATH>" public/svg/{name} --color-map-file public/svg/{name}/ref/color-map.json --recolor-file public/svg/{name}/ref/recolor-map.json
```
